message: Hello future player! To achieve a high score, follow these steps:1. **Cutting Items**: Use the scissors on ingredients. Soft items (natural or artificial) get better when cut ONCE. Hard items (natural or artificial) get worse when cut once, but significantly better when cut TWICE. The scissors appear to be reusable for all cuts in a single round.2. **Combining Items**: After correctly cutting one natural item and one artificial item (e.g., a soft item once, a hard item twice), combine these two prepared items. This combination drastically increases their value.3. **Framing**: Apply the 'frame' tool LAST to your combined item. This will typically boost its value to 100. The frame is consumed after use. Your goal is to cut one natural and one artificial item correctly, combine them, and then frame the result.

message: To achieve a score of 100, follow these steps: First, identify one natural and one artificial item. If an item is soft, cut it once with scissors. Finally, apply the frame to the combined item. The frame must be the very last step, as any subsequent action will ruin it.

message: To achieve the maximum score of 100, follow these steps: First, identify one natural soft item and one artificial soft item. Use the scissors once on each of these (soft items improve when cut once). If you only have one pair of scissors, pick one soft natural item and one *any* artificial item (if the artificial is hard, it won't be improved by scissors once). message: To achieve a perfect score of 100: First, cut one soft natural item with scissors. Second, cut one soft artificial item with scissors. Third, combine these two 'cut' items.
